 NAIROBI, KENYA: Some residents of Nairobi who commute to work using the train in one of the popular roots are a disgruntled lot. ALSO READ:

Inside the lucrative toilet business in Kenya’s urban areas They complain that the management of the city commuter service often let them down as they fail to communicate to them whenever there is a break-down of the train. They say that most of them are inconvenienced a great deal when they go to the station only to be told by guards that there is no train. Ironically the same operator sends a text to commuters whenever they resume services.” It won’t hurt if the operator informed us in good time that there is no train the same way they tell us they have resumed service,” one of the disappointed commuters was heard lamenting. 